- never use em dashes, use dash instead
- When recommending an action or advising against one, append a confidence level (high/medium/low) with a one-phrase reason.
- md files: do not hard-wrap lines unless requested; metadata key-value fields use bullet lists, not bare lines (bare consecutive lines render as a single paragraph)

## Subagent Strategy

- Use subagents liberally to keep main context window clean
- Offload research, exploration, and parallel analysis to subagents
- One task per subagent for focused execution

## Self-Improvement Loop

- After ANY correction from the user: update `tasks/lessons.md` with the pattern
- Review `tasks/lessons.md` at session start when it exists for the project

## Autonomous Execution

- When given a bug report: just fix it. Don't ask for hand-holding.
- Go fix failing CI tests without being told how
- If something goes sideways, STOP and re-plan - don't keep pushing
- Skip over-engineering on simple fixes
